 {"id":"asupersync-28c51.302.43","title":"[peer-review][websocket] Review live cancellation-checkpoint diff for websocket client/server/split","description":"Bounded fresh-eyes review of the current uncommitted websocket cancellation-checkpoint changes in src/net/websocket/{client,server,split}.rs. Goal: verify whether replacing is_cancel_requested() with checkpoint().is_err() is semantically sound in top-level send/recv/connect paths and lower-level poll-time I/O helpers, especially around masked cancellation, checkpoint/progress accounting, and close-handshake behavior. Patch only if a concrete regression is proven; otherwise close with a SOUND/no-regression verdict and focused validation notes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"TealBeaver","created_at":"2026-04-12T02:06:34.281245851Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-12T02:34:17.872441774Z","closed_at":"2026-04-12T02:34:17.871911989Z","close_reason":"Reviewed websocket checkpoint diff, found it semantically sound, added masked-cancellation regression coverage in client/server/split, and repaired split.rs formatting in the touched poll_fn hunk. Remote validation through rch was blocked by unrelated workspace failures in src/service/reconnect.rs and src/grpc/* plus unrelated fmt drift in src/database/postgres.rs/src/grpc/codec.rs/src/process.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.43","depends_on_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-12T02:06:34.281245851Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
